name: Aalim Muhammed Salegh College of Engineering,Chennai
description: There are almost 10 academic departments in this college namely Civil Engineering,Computer Science & Engineering,Electrical & Electronics Engineering,Electronics & Communication Engineering,Information Technology,Mechanical Engineering,Master of Computer Application,Science and Humanities and Physical Education.

FAQ.Does the college offer any scholarship t: Yes. The college offers Government scholarships to its students belonging to SC/ST/BC and other minority categories.

FAQ.Can a students apply for TNEA offline?:
Candidates can fill the application form,attach it with all the document required and send it to the below mentioned address before the deadline arrives:
The Secretary
Tamil Nadu Engineering Admissions
Anna University
Chennai - 600025

FAQ.Does the college provide any accommodati: Yes. The college provides hostel facilities for boys and girls coming from out of the city.

FAQ.What are the organizations by which the: The college has been recognized and approved by All India Council for Technical Education accredited by the National Assessment and Accreditation Council (NAAC).

FAQ.Which university is Aalim Muhammed Saleg: Aalim Muhammed Salegh College of Engineering is affiliated to Anna University.

name: Abdul Kalam Institute of Technology and Science
ABES Engineering College,Ghaziabad
description: Admission in courses offered by the ABES Engineering College is based on merit,last qualifying exam and entrance. For admission in M. Tech students having GATE score are given preference over others. Admission in B. Tech is based on JEE score,for MCA candidates shall possess a valid UP CET score. MBA admission is based on marks obtained in CMAT.
Address: 19th KM Stone,NH-24,Delhi-Hapur Bypass Road,Vijay Nagar,Ghaziabad,Uttar Pradesh,201009

FAQ.When was ABES Engineering College establ: ABES Engineering College was established in 2000.

FAQ.What is the highest package offered at A: The highest package offered at ABES Engineering College is INR 47.20 LPA.

FAQ.What is the eligibility of B. Tech at AB: Candidates who have passed 10+2 with minimum 45% aggregate marks in Science and possess a valid JEE score are eligible to seek admission in B. Tech offered at ABES Engineering College.

FAQ.What is the address of ABES Engineering: The address of ABES Engineering College is 19th KM Stone,NH-09,Ghaziabad,Uttar Pradesh 201009.

FAQ.Who are the top recruiters of ABES Engin: Leading recruiters of ABES Engineering College are TCS,Microsoft,Capgemini,Cognizant,Wipro,BYJUs,Deloitte,Wipro,HCL,OYO,etc.

name: AISSMS College of Engineering,Pune
description: The All India Shri Shivaji Memorial Society’s is the founder trust of the AISSMS College of Engineering,which established the institute in the year 1992 at the city of Pune. Serving the society by keeping the ethics of Chhatrapati Shri Shahu Maharaj from more the decades is one of the leading engineering institutes of the region.History of AISSMS College of Engineering:The story of the establishment of AISSMS College of Engineering lies long back in the year 1917 when the All India Shri Shivaji Memorial Society (AISSMS) was established by HH Shrimant Shri Shahu Chhatrapati Maharaj of Kolhapur to cater the social needs of higher education. The society aimed to find a result-oriented Society which will fulfill the educational needs of Military,General,Technical & Management Education of the country. The society works beyond any race,caste,creed,religion,financial status and political spirit of the person.Quick facts about AISSMS College of Engineering:OwnershipPrivateEngineering RatingAAACampus Area11 AcresTotal Faculty115Total Enrollment3096Set up with the vision to serve the society with quality education and to boost the national wealth by overall upliftment of the society through high-quality education and research the courses offered at AISSMS College of Engineering includes various specialization of technical education. The institute offers 4-year Bachelor of Engineering (BE) degree in eight different streams and 2-year postgraduate degree programme in seven streams of engineering.Below is the list of courses offered and total intake of AISSMS COE:Undergraduate CoursesAnnual IntakePostgraduate CoursesAnnual IntakeChemical Engineering60Chemical Engineering18Civil Engineering120Civil Engineering: Structure18Computer Engineering60Computer Engineering18Computer Engineering 2nd Shift60 - Electrical Engineering60Electrical Engineering: Power Electronics and Drives18Electronics Engineering60Electronics and Telecommunication Engineering: Microwaves18Mechanical Engineering120Mechanical Engineering: Automotive18Mechanical Engineering (Sandwich)60Mechanical Engineering: Design18Production Engineering (Sandwich)60 - Total Intake660Total Intake126AISSMS College of Engineering focuses on providing world-class facilities to its students. The institute has dedicated central library and computer laboratory with the global facilities to aid student’s learning process. Combining classroom education with industrial exposure AISSMS COE collaborated with industries throughout the country and provide internship,skill development,motivational session,and others to create a well-trained professional which will fulfill the needs to industries. Here you can also check about the AISSMS college of engineering cutoff 2023.Student Activities:Research and Development: The core research in the technical fields has been carried out at the well-equipped laboratories of the college under the guidance of trained guides. Several research projects are ongoing at the institute.National Symposium: Every year the institute organizes National Symposium on the trending topics like Durability of Concrete,Advances in Bioprocess Engineering,Power for Sustainable Development and Advances in Automotive Engineering for the engineering professionals.AISSMS Engineering Today: In collaboration with leading industries and organizations,AISSMS organizes National Level Students’ Symposium and Exposition for all-round development of the student.
